{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8059ec1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1001"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1001"},"text":"§ 1001.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Basic entitlement to benefits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Every individual who is a qualified individual under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1002"},"text":"section 1002 of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall, in accordance with and subject to the provisions of this subchapter, be entitled to a monthly benefit paid by the Commissioner of Social Security for each month after September 2000 (or such earlier month, if the Commissioner determines is administratively feasible) the individual resides outside the United States."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8059ec2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title VIII, § 801, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/169/tII/s251/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–169, title II, § 251(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-12-14"},"text":"Dec. 14, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1844"},"text":"113 Stat. 1844","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8059ec3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8059ec4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idb8059ec5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Prior sections 1001 to 1011, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531/tVIII"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531, title VIII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 801–811, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/636-639"},"text":"49 Stat. 636–639","children":[],"tail":", related to taxes with respect to employment. Section 4 of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1939-02-10/ch2"},"text":"act Feb. 10, 1939, ch. 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/53/1"},"text":"53 Stat. 1","children":[],"tail":", which act enacted Title 26, Internal Revenue Code of 1939, provided that all laws and parts of laws codified into the I.R.C. 1939, to the extent that they related exclusively to internal revenue laws, were repealed. Provisions of I.R.C. 1939 were generally repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s7851"},"text":"section 7851 of Title 26","children":[],"tail":", Internal Revenue Code of 1954 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736"},"text":"act Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68A/3"},"text":"68A Stat. 3","children":[],"tail":"). See, also, section 7807 of said Title 26, I.R.C. 1954, respecting rules in effect upon enactment of I.R.C. 1954. The I.R.C. 1954 was redesignated I.R.C. 1986 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2095"},"text":"100 Stat. 2095","children":[],"tail":". The omitted sections were formerly and are now covered by certain sections in Title 26, I.R.C. 1939 and I.R.C. 1986, respectively, as follows:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{},"